WEBVTT

00:03.080 --> 00:04.250
Previously on "How To Get Away
With Murder"...

00:04.250 --> 00:05.080
We're planning
your joint bachelor party!

00:05.080 --> 00:06.790
My mom
is coming on Friday.

00:06.790 --> 00:08.420
I invited
your mom, too.

00:08.420 --> 00:10.710
The jury finds
Nathaniel Calvin Lahey

00:10.710 --> 00:12.540
not guilty
by reason of insanity.

00:12.540 --> 00:14.920
The judge is gonna place you
in a mental facility.

00:14.920 --> 00:16.420
Annalise: I respect
Governor Birkhead.

00:16.420 --> 00:18.540
I'm just one little
defense attorney

00:18.540 --> 00:19.830
that keeps
beating her in court.

00:19.830 --> 00:22.170
-Bring her in.
-We're gonna talk to Annalise.

00:22.170 --> 00:24.330
About Gabriel?
Who the hell is he?

00:24.330 --> 00:26.880
-Where the hell are you?
-Outside Julie's.

00:26.880 --> 00:29.080
-Hey.
-Oliver.

00:29.080 --> 00:30.080
Mom?

00:30.080 --> 00:31.710
♪♪

00:31.710 --> 00:34.080
♪ Whoa ♪

00:34.080 --> 00:38.830
♪♪

00:38.830 --> 00:41.120
♪ Whoa ♪

00:41.120 --> 00:43.120
♪ Three, four, four ♪

00:43.120 --> 00:46.670
♪ Gonna play your drum ♪
♪ Gonna play your drum ♪

00:46.670 --> 00:53.830
♪♪

00:53.830 --> 01:01.120
♪♪

01:01.120 --> 01:03.670
[ Cellphone chimes ]

01:03.670 --> 01:05.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:05.210 --> 01:11.330
♪♪

01:11.330 --> 01:19.080
♪♪

01:19.080 --> 01:21.580
[ Door creaks ]

01:21.580 --> 01:26.580
♪♪

01:26.580 --> 01:28.460
Is this about
Dad being dead?

01:28.460 --> 01:30.500
'Cause I already
know that.

01:30.500 --> 01:31.750
No.

01:31.750 --> 01:33.620
Mom finally die?

01:33.620 --> 01:35.000
I need you to sit.

01:35.000 --> 01:36.210
Are you gonna
throw me some money?

01:36.210 --> 01:38.500
'Cause those are
the only excuses

01:38.500 --> 01:39.880
for you showing up
out of nowhere

01:39.880 --> 01:42.670
after a freakin' decade.

01:42.670 --> 01:44.670
Mommy?

01:44.670 --> 01:47.960
Skyler, what are you
doing up?

01:47.960 --> 01:50.000
You woke me.

01:50.000 --> 01:51.710
Who's that?

01:51.710 --> 01:53.880
That's my sister,
Bonnie.

01:57.540 --> 01:58.830
She's your aunt.

02:01.330 --> 02:03.330
-Who's the father?
-Some deadbeat.

02:03.330 --> 02:04.540
He left before
she gave birth.

02:04.540 --> 02:05.540
Did you tell Bonnie?

02:08.120 --> 02:09.540
What's wrong with you?

02:09.540 --> 02:11.080
I didn't wanna give her
more reason to go there.

02:11.080 --> 02:13.330
She's gonna see that little girl
and never want to leave her.

02:13.330 --> 02:15.290
She's got her boyfriend.
She'll be okay.

02:15.290 --> 02:21.540
♪♪

02:21.540 --> 02:23.420
I need to stay here.

02:23.420 --> 02:24.210
Why?

02:24.210 --> 02:26.540
She has a little girl.

02:26.540 --> 02:29.040
I had no idea.

02:29.040 --> 02:31.580
So I couldn't
talk to her yet.

02:31.580 --> 02:33.580
Annalise: And you think
that man can handle this?

02:33.580 --> 02:35.960
She loves the guy.
She doesn't know him.

02:35.960 --> 02:38.040
You have to go there
and make sure Bonnie's okay.

02:38.040 --> 02:40.120
Julie's clean now.
Maybe the kid's a good sign.

02:40.120 --> 02:41.420
The thought of Julie
having a kid

02:41.420 --> 02:42.960
is the scariest thing
I've ever heard.

02:42.960 --> 02:44.540
That doesn't mean Bonnie
can't handle this on her own.

02:44.540 --> 02:46.040
Bonnie isn't Bonnie
when she's around her sister.

02:46.040 --> 02:47.420
I've seen it.

02:47.420 --> 02:49.330
She turns back into
that abused little girl

02:49.330 --> 02:51.710
desperate to save everyone
but herself.

02:51.710 --> 02:53.500
I don't feel good
about this.

02:54.710 --> 02:56.210
Listen...

02:57.710 --> 03:00.080
...I love you,

03:00.080 --> 03:02.790
and I love
that you came,

03:02.790 --> 03:04.670
but now
I can handle this.

03:04.670 --> 03:13.170
♪♪

03:13.170 --> 03:21.920
♪♪

03:21.920 --> 03:30.960
♪♪

03:30.960 --> 03:33.500
Okay, we know
it's not conventional,

03:33.500 --> 03:35.330
but it's
affordable.

03:35.330 --> 03:38.670
And we can kill two birds
with one venue.

03:38.670 --> 03:39.830
Yeah, the ceremony
and reception.

03:39.830 --> 03:41.080
It's cool, right?

03:41.080 --> 03:42.880
Oh! [ Giggles ]

03:42.880 --> 03:45.710
Oh, honey, I'm just
so happy for you two.

03:45.710 --> 03:48.170
Never in my life did I believe
this day would come.

03:48.170 --> 03:50.210
Why? 'Cause I'm such
a disaster?

03:50.210 --> 03:52.960
No, 'cause I thought
there was never a man
who could lock you down.

03:52.960 --> 03:54.830
-Mm.
-[ Chuckles ] Bravo, Oliver.

03:54.830 --> 03:56.250
[ Chuckles ]

03:56.250 --> 03:58.710
Mom,
what do you think?

03:58.710 --> 04:00.290
You really
want to know?

04:00.290 --> 04:02.330
It'll look better
once we decorate.

04:02.330 --> 04:04.920
Yeah, just a picture --
a photo booth over there

04:04.920 --> 04:06.330
and, you know,
flowers.

04:06.330 --> 04:08.830
And it's cheap,
which is good,

04:08.830 --> 04:10.620
considering our bank accounts
right now.

04:11.830 --> 04:12.880
I have some savings.

04:12.880 --> 04:14.540
Mom, no. We've --

04:14.540 --> 04:16.460
I get to spend my money
on what I want.

04:16.460 --> 04:18.080
That's not
really the point --

04:18.080 --> 04:20.580
Y-You know what, um, Connor?
I actually am with Joanna.

04:20.580 --> 04:23.040
Why don't we take a look
at some other venues?

04:23.040 --> 04:25.540
We're all here together.
Might be fun.

04:25.540 --> 04:27.880
Yeah,
th-that's a great idea.

04:27.880 --> 04:29.460
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

04:29.460 --> 04:31.500
Or we could just try
to make this place work,

04:31.500 --> 04:34.500
you know, 'cause a wedding's
not about a location.

04:34.500 --> 04:36.210
It's about
who we invite,

04:36.210 --> 04:39.830
and you will both
be there, so...

04:39.830 --> 04:41.210
Whatever you say.

04:41.210 --> 04:46.960
♪♪

04:46.960 --> 04:48.880
He's good, but who knew
he was gonna be that good?

04:48.880 --> 04:51.620
Oh, and he looks damn good
in a suit!
[ Chuckles ]

04:51.620 --> 04:58.540
♪♪

04:58.540 --> 04:59.790
[ Cellphone ringing ]

05:02.830 --> 05:03.830
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:03.830 --> 05:05.210
Hi.

05:05.210 --> 05:06.620
Frank: You stalking him
right now?

05:06.620 --> 05:08.420
Of course not.

05:08.420 --> 05:10.290
Don't lie to me.

05:10.290 --> 05:12.710
How have you kept this
a secret for this long?

05:12.710 --> 05:15.080
I do what I got to do
to keep us safe.

05:15.080 --> 05:17.420
Now it's your job since
you had to get all nosey.

05:17.420 --> 05:20.080
I would do anything
to not know this.

05:20.080 --> 05:22.460
And who do you have
to blame for that?

05:22.460 --> 05:23.920
Just play dumb
while I head out of town.

05:23.920 --> 05:25.460
Where are you going?

05:25.460 --> 05:27.250
You really want to know?

05:27.250 --> 05:28.670
Good point. Never mind.

05:28.670 --> 05:29.830
Now you're learning.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.380
Hey. Do you know
what we're doing today?

05:31.380 --> 05:32.500
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:32.500 --> 05:34.670
No. But Annalise
isn't here.

05:34.670 --> 05:35.830
Should we play hooky?

05:35.830 --> 05:37.750
Tegan:
iCállate y escucha bien!

05:37.750 --> 05:40.000
Professor Keating has
a professional obligation,

05:40.000 --> 05:41.670
so I'm your boss
for the day.

05:41.670 --> 05:43.290
Our client Gut Suckers

05:43.290 --> 05:47.120
is being sued for $100 million
in punitive damages

05:47.120 --> 05:49.710
for making false claims
about their diet pills.

05:49.710 --> 05:51.380
The only false claim is to say
these pills actually work.

05:51.380 --> 05:53.500
I don't care if they work.
I care about

05:53.500 --> 05:55.330
preventing our client
from going bankrupt.

05:55.330 --> 05:56.880
In these boxes
are trial records

05:56.880 --> 05:59.170
for every lawsuit brought
against a diet pill company.

05:59.170 --> 06:01.620
Find the best strategy
and bring it to me.

06:01.620 --> 06:03.420
I need someone
to run point.
I can do it.

06:03.420 --> 06:05.250
Ms. Castillo,
you're taking lead.

06:05.250 --> 06:07.380
I want a full report
by 5:00 p.m.

06:07.380 --> 06:09.380
Um...

06:09.380 --> 06:10.330
Ms. Price.

06:11.960 --> 06:13.420
[ Quietly ]
Uh, Michaela actually has

06:13.420 --> 06:15.170
a lot more experience
in civil cases.

06:15.170 --> 06:16.710
[ Quietly ] Your family
almost destroyed this firm.

06:16.710 --> 06:17.920
That's why we have to take
low-rent accounts

06:17.920 --> 06:19.080
like Gut Suckers.

06:20.040 --> 06:21.710
It's about time
you paid us all back.

06:21.710 --> 06:31.040
♪♪

06:31.040 --> 06:33.080
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

06:34.880 --> 06:36.120
[ Door opens ]

06:36.120 --> 06:39.120
Ms. Keating,
we meet at last.

06:39.120 --> 06:41.580
Governor.

06:41.580 --> 06:43.960
Can I be candid
with you?

06:43.960 --> 06:46.790
I expect nothing less.

06:46.790 --> 06:49.250
I was pissed when I saw
your last press conference.

06:49.250 --> 06:51.750
I was screaming
at the television.

06:51.750 --> 06:54.830
My entire staff
was hiding from me.

06:54.830 --> 06:56.080
I don't like to lose.

06:56.080 --> 06:57.620
Who does?

06:57.620 --> 07:00.250
And that's why
I brought you here today.

07:00.250 --> 07:02.830
To say
that I-I was wrong.

07:02.830 --> 07:05.460
I want us to work together,
Annalise.

07:05.460 --> 07:07.790
All this time, all you've done
is work against me.

07:07.790 --> 07:09.460
And look
at the outcome --

07:09.460 --> 07:12.210
public opinion is
on your side, not mine.

07:12.210 --> 07:14.420
I had to just
take a step back

07:14.420 --> 07:16.790
and do some soul-searching
and prayer,

07:16.790 --> 07:20.000
and I-I came up
with a very simple truth.

07:20.000 --> 07:21.960
Our state can do better.

07:21.960 --> 07:24.330
I can do better.

07:24.330 --> 07:26.920
So, here's my pitch.

07:26.920 --> 07:29.080
I want you and I
to work together

07:29.080 --> 07:33.500
to create the Pennsylvania
Fair Defense Project.

07:33.500 --> 07:35.710
As head of the project,
you'd allocate funds

07:35.710 --> 07:39.170
for public defenders,
create caseload caps.

07:39.170 --> 07:42.290
Most important --
I want you to draft a bill

07:42.290 --> 07:46.000
to reduce the prison
population by 50% --

07:46.000 --> 07:48.750
a law that could be adopted
by every state in the nation

07:48.750 --> 07:50.210
if we get it right.

07:50.210 --> 07:52.120
The catch?

07:52.120 --> 07:55.120
Besides having to work
hand-in-hand with a Republican?

07:55.120 --> 07:57.120
[ Chuckles ]

07:57.120 --> 08:00.040
It's great publicity
for your re-election, I agree,

08:00.040 --> 08:01.960
but I'm doing this work
already.

08:01.960 --> 08:04.380
Yeah, but not with the power
of this office behind you.

08:04.380 --> 08:07.000
I just signed a contract
with Caplan & Gold.

08:07.000 --> 08:08.380
I can get you
out of that.

08:08.380 --> 08:10.210
Mm.

08:10.210 --> 08:12.420
And don't worry
about your law clinic.

08:12.420 --> 08:13.710
We want you
to hire your students

08:13.710 --> 08:15.000
to work on this project.

08:16.420 --> 08:20.040
Now, I'll need your decision
within two days,

08:20.040 --> 08:22.290
and until then,
this stays confidential.

08:22.290 --> 08:29.290
♪♪

08:29.290 --> 08:30.460
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

08:30.460 --> 08:32.460
[ Door opens, creaks ]

08:32.460 --> 08:33.880
[ Door closes,
vibrating continues ]

08:33.880 --> 08:37.500
Julie:
I picked up some food on the way
home from Skyler's school.

08:37.500 --> 08:39.920
Thought about
buying booze

08:39.920 --> 08:42.170
to finally get you
to spill why you're here,

08:42.170 --> 08:44.880
but can't be risking
my sobriety,

08:44.880 --> 08:46.380
even for you.

08:48.540 --> 08:55.380
♪♪

08:55.380 --> 08:56.960
You said he was dead.

08:56.960 --> 09:00.920
♪♪

09:00.920 --> 09:04.540
Y-You...

09:04.540 --> 09:07.080
lost all that blood.

09:07.080 --> 09:10.460
Mom and Dad were freaking out,
I was alone with the baby,

09:10.460 --> 09:12.170
and I-I did
what we talked about.

09:12.170 --> 09:13.670
I left him
at the hospital.

09:15.750 --> 09:17.670
You're taking him
from the hospital here.

09:17.670 --> 09:24.830
♪♪

09:24.830 --> 09:27.380
Dad...

09:27.380 --> 09:30.380
beat it out of me.

09:30.380 --> 09:31.880
Told some nurse
I was the mother,

09:31.880 --> 09:33.670
and they let me
take him.

09:33.670 --> 09:36.540
But...
when we got home...

09:38.830 --> 09:41.290
...Dad drove him
somewhere.

09:41.290 --> 09:42.920
Mom said he sold him.

09:42.920 --> 09:44.120
To who?

09:45.710 --> 09:48.290
I don't know.

09:48.290 --> 09:50.790
They just said...
[sniffles]

09:50.790 --> 09:54.580
they'd kill me
if I ever told you.

09:54.580 --> 09:57.380
I just never wanted you
to worry about him.

09:57.380 --> 09:59.670
That's all this was --

09:59.670 --> 10:01.420
making sure
you never had to worry.

10:01.420 --> 10:03.000
I swear, Bonnie.

10:03.000 --> 10:08.790
♪♪

10:08.790 --> 10:10.880
[ Sobbing ]

10:10.880 --> 10:13.120
♪♪

10:17.500 --> 10:18.880
Don't tell me you believe
a word of that story.

10:18.880 --> 10:20.210
I never said
I believed her.

10:20.210 --> 10:22.250
So, why are you still there?
For the little girl?

10:22.250 --> 10:23.540
I came
all the way out here.

10:23.540 --> 10:25.120
I'm not leaving
until I know more.

10:25.120 --> 10:26.750
That's what Julie wants!

10:26.750 --> 10:28.460
She'll say whatever she needs
to suck you back in.

10:28.460 --> 10:29.830
You said that
you would support me

10:29.830 --> 10:31.040
no matter what I wanted.

10:31.040 --> 10:32.250
Well, I want
to know more,

10:32.250 --> 10:34.120
and that's
going to take time.

10:34.120 --> 10:35.380
You know her.

10:35.380 --> 10:36.540
[ Horn honks ]

10:39.080 --> 10:40.790
I think
you should come home.

10:40.790 --> 10:43.080
[ Door creaks ]

10:43.080 --> 10:44.750
[ Door closes ]
I'll call you later.

10:44.750 --> 10:47.000
[ Clicks ]

10:47.000 --> 10:48.790
Annalise?

10:48.790 --> 10:50.000
Where you going?

10:50.000 --> 10:51.750
N.A.

10:51.750 --> 10:53.000
Julie.

10:55.080 --> 10:57.750
All I want to do is
get high right now,

10:57.750 --> 11:01.420
so trust me,
I'm doing what's good for me.

11:01.420 --> 11:03.500
[ Engine starts,
car door opens ]

11:03.500 --> 11:13.330
♪♪

11:13.330 --> 11:16.500
I know you're frustrated.
I understand.

11:16.500 --> 11:20.170
They just don't have any rooms
at the hospital yet.

11:20.170 --> 11:22.170
I'm gonna
talk to D.A. Miller

11:22.170 --> 11:23.580
about getting you
moved up the waitlist.

11:25.460 --> 11:26.960
[ Sighs ]

11:26.960 --> 11:28.170
It's karma.

11:30.960 --> 11:34.330
Never made things right
with that man's family.

11:34.330 --> 11:37.250
Seeing those photos
at the trial...

11:37.250 --> 11:39.000
Ohh. [ Clicks tongue ]

11:39.000 --> 11:41.710
...things I'd done
to him.

11:41.710 --> 11:43.420
[ Sighs ]

11:45.500 --> 11:48.080
I need to write
that family a letter.

11:48.080 --> 11:50.710
It's been 30 years.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.000
You've done your time.

11:54.080 --> 11:55.920
Just find me
somebody to write to.

11:57.920 --> 11:59.500
Please, son.

11:59.500 --> 12:08.790
♪♪

12:08.790 --> 12:18.250
♪♪

12:18.250 --> 12:19.670
[ Door opens ]

12:19.670 --> 12:22.420
Oh, you -- you don't
need to hide that.

12:22.420 --> 12:24.540
Yeah, so, uh, I got off
my plane from London

12:24.540 --> 12:26.210
to a message from
an old Hotchkiss classmate

12:26.210 --> 12:28.420
whose wife works
for the Governor.

12:28.420 --> 12:29.880
[ Door closes ]

12:29.880 --> 12:33.500
I had no clue why she wanted
to see me until I got there.

12:33.500 --> 12:34.750
So, you turned her down?

12:36.290 --> 12:38.040
What is this about?
Do you want more money?!

12:38.040 --> 12:39.420
Do you enjoy
humiliating me?!

12:39.420 --> 12:41.330
Lower your voice.
No, you signed a contract,

12:41.330 --> 12:42.670
and I will sue your ass
if you leave!

12:42.670 --> 12:44.920
And I'll sue you back for
verbal abuse in the workplace,

12:44.920 --> 12:46.790
and it looks like I have
a few witnesses here, too.

12:46.790 --> 12:48.830
[ Clears throat ]
You think the board
wants to hear

12:48.830 --> 12:50.540
that you've committed
more misconduct?

12:53.880 --> 12:56.040
This is the same governor
I've been protecting you from

12:56.040 --> 12:57.420
since we hired you.

12:57.420 --> 12:59.460
I took this job
for the sole purpose

12:59.460 --> 13:02.620
to reform the Dumpster fire that
is our public defense system.

13:02.620 --> 13:04.880
And, yes, maybe you've put
your ass on the line for me,

13:04.880 --> 13:06.500
but I am
no man's savior.

13:06.500 --> 13:08.250
I've worked too long
and too hard

13:08.250 --> 13:10.420
to get an ounce of power
in this world,

13:10.420 --> 13:12.880
and your ass sure as
hell is not gonna decide
what's right for me.

13:15.500 --> 13:17.920
I'll let you know
when I've made my decision.

13:17.920 --> 13:25.290
♪♪

13:25.290 --> 13:26.420
[ Door closes ]

13:26.420 --> 13:28.380
[ Birds chirping, dog barking ]

13:28.380 --> 13:30.080
Is it okay
if I call you Mom, Mom?

13:30.080 --> 13:32.380
-No.
-Of course, Asher.

13:32.380 --> 13:34.880
Yes, I was already so excited
to add Oliver to the family.

13:34.880 --> 13:37.500
-Why not one more son?
-You hear that, C-dog?

13:37.500 --> 13:39.500
Not only are we BFFs,
but we're brothers now, too.

13:39.500 --> 13:40.710
-Hm.
-You.

13:40.710 --> 13:42.620
Hey, Connor?
[ Glasses clink ]

13:42.620 --> 13:44.790
[ Slurps ]

13:44.790 --> 13:46.960
[ Whispering ] Remind me
why we invited him.

13:46.960 --> 13:48.250
Uh, just keep him away
from my mother.

13:48.250 --> 13:49.960
She already thinks
he's too friendly.

13:49.960 --> 13:51.460
Oh, so I'm not the only one
she hates. Good.

13:51.460 --> 13:53.250
About that --
She hates me.
Don't lie.

13:53.250 --> 13:54.420
You work with Annalise
every day.

13:54.420 --> 13:55.920
You can easily
handle my mother.

13:58.290 --> 14:00.000
Hey, Mom, Connor's never
had lumpia before.

14:00.000 --> 14:01.380
Maybe you can show him
how it's made.

14:01.380 --> 14:03.000
There won't be
any lumpia

14:03.000 --> 14:04.500
unless someone makes
this stove work.

14:04.500 --> 14:06.120
Oh, yeah, there's
a little trick to it.

14:06.120 --> 14:07.750
[ Clicking ]

14:07.750 --> 14:10.210
I know you had to move here
to save money for the wedding,

14:10.210 --> 14:12.000
but you want to know
another solution?

14:12.000 --> 14:13.750
Get married in a church.
They're cheap.

14:13.750 --> 14:15.500
Mom, we have already
talked about this.

14:15.500 --> 14:17.040
You think God hates you.
I know.

14:17.040 --> 14:18.750
That is not
what I said.

14:18.750 --> 14:20.080
Why not ask your father
for money?

14:20.080 --> 14:22.620
-[ Sighing ] Oh, God.
-Oliver told me he's rich.

14:22.620 --> 14:23.830
He and I aren't
that close anymore.

14:23.830 --> 14:25.170
Hm.

14:26.460 --> 14:27.790
Of course you can come
to the bachelor party.

14:27.790 --> 14:28.790
The more
the merrier!

14:28.790 --> 14:30.000
-Oh, God, no.
-Asher.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.080
Don't be mad at Asher.
I forced him to tell me.

14:32.080 --> 14:34.000
What mom goes to
their son's bachelor party?

14:34.000 --> 14:35.750
The cool moms,
that's who.

14:35.750 --> 14:37.120
Joanna and I are gonna be
on our best behavior,

14:37.120 --> 14:38.750
isn't that right,
Jo-Jo?

14:40.460 --> 14:41.830
Oops.

14:41.830 --> 14:44.830
♪♪

14:44.830 --> 14:47.040
Male announcer:
Stop sucking in that gut
and shrink it instead!

14:47.040 --> 14:48.960
Woman: Gut Suckers is
the only weight-loss pill

14:48.960 --> 14:51.380
that actually blocks one-third
of the calories you consume

14:51.380 --> 14:52.830
from being digested.

14:52.830 --> 14:54.330
Go ahead. Enjoy life!

14:54.330 --> 14:56.460
[ Click ]

14:56.460 --> 14:58.830
Did you hear that?
Gut Suckers' FDA application

14:58.830 --> 15:02.210
claims that it prevents
one-third of consumed fat,

15:02.210 --> 15:04.500
not calories,
from being digested.

15:04.500 --> 15:07.290
That means that it's
the ad agency's fault,

15:07.290 --> 15:08.420
not our client's.

15:08.420 --> 15:10.210
Why is
Ms. Castillo wrong?

15:10.210 --> 15:11.670
A corporation
assumes liability

15:11.670 --> 15:13.170
for the actions of
its subcontractors,

15:13.170 --> 15:15.210
including branding
and marketing,

15:15.210 --> 15:17.540
which of course
I learned from you.

15:17.540 --> 15:19.170
9:00 a.m. tomorrow,
I want 10 more ideas

15:19.170 --> 15:20.080
better than this one.

15:25.120 --> 15:26.540
You couldn't have
told me that before?

15:26.540 --> 15:27.620
I just remembered.

15:27.620 --> 15:30.380
Or you'll do anything
to impress her

15:30.380 --> 15:31.460
because you're in love
with her.

15:34.330 --> 15:36.380
Hey.

15:36.380 --> 15:38.420
So, looks like it's my turn
to scratch your back.

15:38.420 --> 15:39.790
What?
You helped me

15:39.790 --> 15:41.460
when I was running point
on Senior's case.

15:41.460 --> 15:43.330
It's only right
I return the favor.

15:43.330 --> 15:45.290
I can
come by tonight.

15:45.290 --> 15:47.000
I'm good.

15:47.000 --> 15:48.170
[ Footsteps ]

15:50.290 --> 15:51.880
Miller: I should
be there with you.

15:51.880 --> 15:53.920
You are.
You're talking to me.

15:53.920 --> 15:55.790
Well, then let me find out
if what she said is true.

15:55.790 --> 15:57.670
I can, you know,
look into

15:57.670 --> 15:59.290
where your father was
around that time,

15:59.290 --> 16:01.120
see who he talked to.

16:01.120 --> 16:03.540
You digging around in
any official capacity

16:03.540 --> 16:05.500
could get
her daughter taken away.

16:05.500 --> 16:06.920
Saying things like that

16:06.920 --> 16:08.040
makes me want
to come and rescue you.

16:09.880 --> 16:11.540
What's going on?

16:11.540 --> 16:12.290
Bonnie?

16:14.120 --> 16:15.460
Actually,
I do need your help.

16:15.460 --> 16:19.670
♪♪

16:19.670 --> 16:22.830
So, my baby sister's
in town.

16:22.830 --> 16:24.080
[ Chuckles lightly ]

16:24.080 --> 16:25.880
She...

16:25.880 --> 16:28.750
cut me off
when I was using a lot.

16:28.750 --> 16:30.460
But she's here now

16:30.460 --> 16:33.080
'cause she found out
I've been...

16:33.080 --> 16:35.750
hiding something from her.

16:35.750 --> 16:37.170
She thinks she's the one

16:37.170 --> 16:39.710
that's been protecting me
this whole time,

16:39.710 --> 16:42.500
but really it's
the other way around.

16:42.500 --> 16:45.000
And all I've done

16:45.000 --> 16:47.500
is try to protect her,

16:47.500 --> 16:51.960
to the point that
I kept secrets

16:51.960 --> 16:54.750
that ate me alive,

16:54.750 --> 16:58.330
that made me use.

16:58.330 --> 17:00.290
But the only way
I can tell her that

17:00.290 --> 17:03.170
is to risk
losing her forever,

17:03.170 --> 17:06.880
'cause if she knew
the truth,

17:06.880 --> 17:08.420
it would kill her.

17:08.420 --> 17:10.120
♪♪

17:14.460 --> 17:15.540
You sure there's
nothing I can do?

17:15.540 --> 17:16.960
Frank's there.
We've got it covered.

17:16.960 --> 17:19.080
I'm already inside this case.
I can help.

17:19.080 --> 17:20.380
You've helped
Bonnie enough.

17:20.380 --> 17:22.330
We all have.

17:22.330 --> 17:24.380
But I'm sure you didn't
come here to talk about her.

17:25.670 --> 17:29.250
My pops wants to send a letter
to the Reinhoff family.

17:29.250 --> 17:31.620
I'm looking
for an address,

17:31.620 --> 17:33.750
but if the media gets hold of it
or the Governor --

17:33.750 --> 17:36.330
No, the Governor's
on our side now.

17:36.330 --> 17:38.040
She offered me this job
this morning.

17:41.620 --> 17:42.830
You trust her?

17:42.830 --> 17:44.290
I don't trust anyone.

17:44.290 --> 17:46.330
♪♪

17:46.330 --> 17:48.080
-Christopher.
-[ Chuckles ]

17:48.080 --> 17:49.380
Asher: You want
some lumpia?

17:49.380 --> 17:51.380
When my Oliver
was this age,

17:51.380 --> 17:53.250
strangers would stop us
on the street

17:53.250 --> 17:55.500
and tell me
how beautiful he was.

17:55.500 --> 17:57.250
-People still do that!
-Mmm, Mrs. Hampton,

17:57.250 --> 17:59.170
this is so good.
-Honestly,

17:59.170 --> 18:01.330
I forgot how much I missed
a home-cooked meal.

18:01.330 --> 18:02.920
-Don't you cook for Asher?
-Mom, I told you --

18:02.920 --> 18:04.330
they broke up.

18:04.330 --> 18:06.380
Why'd you do that?
Look at you both.

18:06.380 --> 18:09.170
Talk about making
a beautiful baby.

18:09.170 --> 18:10.540
Aww, that's sweet,
but, uh,

18:10.540 --> 18:12.330
Missy and I here are
better off as friends.

18:12.330 --> 18:14.250
And Michaela's actually
reassessing

18:14.250 --> 18:15.880
her interest in men
these days.

18:15.880 --> 18:17.500
-Wait, what?
-She's kidding.

18:17.500 --> 18:18.920
I'm focused
on work right now,

18:18.920 --> 18:20.540
something that Laurel
should probably do

18:20.540 --> 18:23.250
so that Tegan doesn't fire her
for failing our client.

18:23.250 --> 18:25.250
Some ladies at church
tried Gut Suckers,

18:25.250 --> 18:27.380
and they couldn't get off
the toilet for days.

18:27.380 --> 18:28.420
[ Chuckles ]

18:28.420 --> 18:30.620
They should've called it
a liquid diet.

18:30.620 --> 18:32.790
Mmm, who needs
another drink?

18:32.790 --> 18:34.880
[ Laughter ]

18:34.880 --> 18:36.040
[ Whispering ]
Oh, thank God.

18:36.040 --> 18:37.620
[ Whispering ] What,
did the lumpia get you, too?

18:37.620 --> 18:39.330
Joanna found
a nicer wedding venue,

18:39.330 --> 18:41.080
and she asked if
I would kick in 10 grand

18:41.080 --> 18:42.290
so we could
surprise you.

18:42.290 --> 18:43.790
This is so messed up.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.620
I-I didn't have the guts to
tell her I don't have the money.

18:45.620 --> 18:47.170
Don't you dare feel bad.

18:47.170 --> 18:48.540
She's the one not listening
to what we want.

18:48.540 --> 18:50.210
What? No, I know,
but she just wants you both

18:50.210 --> 18:51.460
to know
how loved you are.

18:51.460 --> 18:53.500
I'm not having a wedding
that I don't want.

18:53.500 --> 18:55.250
Why don't you just talk
to Oliver, all right?

18:55.250 --> 18:56.710
Maybe he can
get through to her.

18:56.710 --> 18:58.500
No, he can't.
He's afraid of her.

18:58.500 --> 19:00.210
[ Clears throat ]

19:02.330 --> 19:04.250
Oliver: You don't understand
what she gave up for me --

19:04.250 --> 19:06.580
her friends,
some family.

19:06.580 --> 19:08.420
That doesn't mean you have to do
everything she says.

19:08.420 --> 19:10.750
Actually, it does.
She never asks me for anything.

19:10.750 --> 19:13.210
She's your mother.
She's not supposed to.

19:13.210 --> 19:14.580
Well, fine,
but you can't be mad at me

19:14.580 --> 19:15.670
for trying to be
a good son.

19:19.170 --> 19:20.540
You need to tell her.

19:20.540 --> 19:23.040
No, I'd just rather have
a big, stupid wedding.

19:23.040 --> 19:24.710
That's not
what I'm talking about.

19:24.710 --> 19:32.460
♪♪

19:32.460 --> 19:35.540
Look,
you are a good son.

19:35.540 --> 19:37.920
That's painfully obvious
after seeing you two together.

19:40.170 --> 19:41.500
[ Sighs ]

19:43.250 --> 19:45.170
Just feels like I have to
come out all over again.

19:46.420 --> 19:47.460
You do.

19:50.120 --> 19:51.620
But this time
you have me.

19:51.620 --> 19:54.920
♪♪

19:54.920 --> 19:56.750
Julie: You hungry?

19:56.750 --> 19:58.580
I can order a pizza
once Skyler's asleep.

20:02.080 --> 20:03.330
[ Sniffs ]
Why do you have this?

20:07.670 --> 20:09.620
The serial number's
unregistered.

20:09.620 --> 20:12.120
So if the police found it,
you would be arrested,

20:12.120 --> 20:14.080
Child Services
would come take Skyler.

20:14.080 --> 20:16.540
I live alone
in a bad part of town.

20:16.540 --> 20:18.380
I may not
be mother of the year,

20:18.380 --> 20:20.290
but she's the only reason
I haven't taken that gun

20:20.290 --> 20:21.750
and blown my brains out.

20:21.750 --> 20:23.120
[ Whispering ]
What about my child?

20:25.120 --> 20:27.540
You promised me
that we would protect him,

20:27.540 --> 20:28.920
and that was
the only thing

20:28.920 --> 20:30.790
that got me through
those nine months, was knowing

20:30.790 --> 20:33.000
that he wouldn't have to go
through what we went through.

20:35.750 --> 20:38.120
[ Whispering ]
We -- We don't know anything bad
happened to him.

20:38.120 --> 20:40.620
[ Voice breaking ]
Someone bought him.

20:40.620 --> 20:42.420
Do you seriously think
they had good intentions?

20:44.750 --> 20:47.460
I'll make it right.

20:47.460 --> 20:49.460
Help you find him
if that's what you want.

20:50.960 --> 20:52.750
We can find him.

20:55.750 --> 20:59.120
Julie: And all I've done
is try to protect her,

20:59.120 --> 21:01.120
but the only way
I can tell her that

21:01.120 --> 21:03.880
is to risk losing her forever,

21:03.880 --> 21:07.960
'cause if she knew the truth,
it would kill her.

21:07.960 --> 21:10.170
Frank:
What do you think?

21:10.170 --> 21:13.040
I think Bonnie was better off
without this in her life.

21:13.040 --> 21:14.540
I mean, what do I do?

21:14.540 --> 21:15.920
Play it for Bonnie?

21:15.920 --> 21:17.120
I don't care.

21:17.120 --> 21:18.420
Of course you do.

21:18.420 --> 21:21.120
Listen, I told her to come home,
she said no,

21:21.120 --> 21:23.380
and I have enough decisions to
make right now, so you decide.

21:23.380 --> 21:24.790
But you're the one
that told me to come here.

21:24.790 --> 21:26.170
Frank!

21:26.170 --> 21:27.670
[ Sighs ]

21:27.670 --> 21:28.830
I'll handle it.

21:28.830 --> 21:37.880
♪♪

21:37.880 --> 21:47.670
♪♪

21:51.330 --> 21:53.250
Are you here
to offer me an apology?

21:53.250 --> 21:55.210
Actually, I'm here
to accept yours.

21:56.880 --> 21:58.330
[ Chuckles ]

21:58.330 --> 22:00.710
Okay, you can't make jokes
if you can't take them.

22:00.710 --> 22:02.960
I was reading over
the Governor's proposal,

22:02.960 --> 22:04.960
and from what I read,

22:04.960 --> 22:07.790
the offer isn't exactly
what Birkhead made it out to be.

22:07.790 --> 22:10.210
Paragraph 12B...
[ Thumps ]

22:10.210 --> 22:12.380
...the project's budget
will be determined

22:12.380 --> 22:13.880
by quarterly targets

22:13.880 --> 22:15.790
to reduce
the incarceration rate.

22:15.790 --> 22:18.250
Failure to meet
those targets

22:18.250 --> 22:21.040
will result in you
having your funding frozen.

22:21.040 --> 22:23.170
This is your best argument
to turn down the job?

22:23.170 --> 22:25.540
This project is
a smokescreen, Annalise.

22:25.540 --> 22:27.120
She knows
she can't beat you,

22:27.120 --> 22:30.710
so she's gonna bury you
in bureaucracy instead.

22:30.710 --> 22:34.290
If you can't see that,
I can't help you.

22:34.290 --> 22:39.920
♪♪

22:39.920 --> 22:46.830
♪♪

22:46.830 --> 22:48.790
[ Ringing ]

22:48.790 --> 22:50.210
Receptionist:
Governor Birkhead's office.

22:50.210 --> 22:51.710
Hi, this is
Annalise Keating.

22:51.710 --> 22:53.580
I was hoping to speak
to Governor Birkhead.

22:53.580 --> 22:55.080
One moment, please.

22:55.080 --> 22:58.540
♪♪

22:58.540 --> 22:59.710
Governor Birkhead:
Ms. Keating.

22:59.710 --> 23:01.540
I was hoping
to hear from you.

23:01.540 --> 23:04.080
Unless you're calling
to turn down my offer.

23:04.080 --> 23:05.750
I have concerns
about the budget,

23:05.750 --> 23:08.170
specifically
paragraph 12B.

23:08.170 --> 23:10.960
You're uncomfortable
with the quarterly targets?

23:10.960 --> 23:12.620
Making change
doesn't come cheap.

23:12.620 --> 23:15.000
I'll need a set budget,
regardless of our progress.

23:15.000 --> 23:16.460
I'll talk to my people.

23:16.460 --> 23:18.040
Anything else
you're bumping on?

23:22.210 --> 23:24.880
I want a pardon
for Nathaniel Lahey Senior.

23:24.880 --> 23:27.460
He's waiting for placement
in a mental-health facility,

23:27.460 --> 23:29.670
but he would prefer
to live with his son.

23:29.670 --> 23:32.210
A pardon would be the only way
to make that happen.

23:32.210 --> 23:35.250
[ Exhale sharply ]
That is a-a bold request.

23:35.250 --> 23:36.500
So is asking me
to work for you.

23:38.250 --> 23:40.250
These decisions
have to be vetted

23:40.250 --> 23:42.710
by the Board of Pardons,
but...

23:42.710 --> 23:45.210
I'll look into it
and see what I can do, okay?

23:46.170 --> 23:47.330
Okay.

23:47.330 --> 23:50.620
♪♪

23:50.620 --> 23:51.620
[ Cellphone beeps ]

23:51.620 --> 23:53.080
[ Cellphone clatters ]

23:57.210 --> 23:59.330
[ Gasps ] Handsome!

23:59.330 --> 24:01.500
I...hate it.

24:01.500 --> 24:02.790
Why?

24:02.790 --> 24:04.170
Too tight
in the crotch?

24:04.170 --> 24:06.040
No, M-- Mom,
let's just look for something

24:06.040 --> 24:07.460
that's a little
more modern.

24:07.460 --> 24:08.960
I don't want to clash
with Connor.

24:08.960 --> 24:12.880
Right, 'cause this wedding
is about what he wants.

24:12.880 --> 24:14.750
Why don't you like him?

24:14.750 --> 24:16.210
Before you met him,

24:16.210 --> 24:18.920
you had a good job,
a good place to live.

24:18.920 --> 24:20.540
It was my idea to move.

24:20.540 --> 24:22.460
How am I supposed to know that
when you never call me?

24:22.460 --> 24:25.420
Come on.
We talk every few weeks.

24:25.420 --> 24:27.210
We used to talk
every day.

24:27.210 --> 24:29.670
So what happened?

24:29.670 --> 24:31.170
Did I do something
to make you mad?

24:33.040 --> 24:34.080
Or is it him?

24:37.960 --> 24:40.540
Mom, Connor's not the reason
that I've been pulling away.

24:40.540 --> 24:41.830
Are you sure?

24:41.830 --> 24:43.000
He's very bossy.

24:43.000 --> 24:44.620
[ Laughs ]

24:44.620 --> 24:48.250
Um, I've been avoiding
telling you something.

24:48.250 --> 24:51.330
♪♪

24:51.330 --> 24:55.000
First of all, uh,
I'm -- I'm fine, and...

24:55.000 --> 24:56.920
[exhales deeply]
healthy.

24:56.920 --> 24:58.290
Healthy?
Why wouldn't you be healthy?

25:00.920 --> 25:02.540
I'm HIV positive.

25:04.250 --> 25:06.880
Th-- I-I'm undetectable,

25:06.880 --> 25:09.960
which means that the --
the -- the medicine is working,

25:09.960 --> 25:11.290
and so that's good,

25:11.290 --> 25:14.170
and I'm gonna live
a happy, healthy life

25:14.170 --> 25:17.880
for a long time,
just like everybody else, so...

25:17.880 --> 25:20.880
I just didn't tell you
so you wouldn't worry.

25:20.880 --> 25:23.500
But you not telling me
does make me worry.

25:23.500 --> 25:25.250
Mom, the first thing
you told me when I came out

25:25.250 --> 25:27.080
is that you wanted me
to be safe.

25:29.040 --> 25:32.210
We both know
what that meant.

25:32.210 --> 25:33.880
And I...

25:35.880 --> 25:38.120
...and I am --
I am safe,

25:38.120 --> 25:39.920
e-even though
this happened.

25:39.920 --> 25:41.330
Just...

25:44.960 --> 25:47.210
I'm ashamed
that it happened.

25:49.120 --> 25:53.710
[ Sniffles ] Even though
I don't want to be, but...

25:53.710 --> 25:55.750
I guess I just hate
disappointing people,

25:55.750 --> 25:56.920
especially you.

25:56.920 --> 26:00.170
So...
I'm -- I'm sorry.

26:01.380 --> 26:03.080
And I shouldn't say that.

26:03.080 --> 26:05.210
This doesn't have to be
such a big deal, but, um...

26:05.210 --> 26:08.620
I'm -- I'm --
I'm really sorry.

26:08.620 --> 26:14.880
♪♪

26:14.880 --> 26:17.170
Look at me.

26:17.170 --> 26:19.250
Oliver.

26:19.250 --> 26:20.620
Look at me.

26:20.620 --> 26:26.330
♪♪

26:26.330 --> 26:30.210
I'm here for you
until the day I die,

26:30.210 --> 26:31.670
no matter what.

26:35.040 --> 26:37.380
I just hate
that you felt

26:37.380 --> 26:39.420
you had to go through this
all alone.

26:42.670 --> 26:44.170
I wasn't alone.

26:44.170 --> 26:45.670
I had Connor.

26:47.170 --> 26:48.580
[ Exhales shakily ]

26:52.460 --> 26:54.710
Then he should've
told me.

26:54.710 --> 26:56.040
[ Laughs ]

26:56.040 --> 27:02.620
♪♪

27:02.620 --> 27:04.460
[ Sniffles ]

27:04.460 --> 27:07.670
♪♪

27:07.670 --> 27:09.500
Let's hear it,
Ms. Castillo.

27:09.500 --> 27:12.080
Or am I gonna have to tell
Keating you're a failure?

27:12.080 --> 27:13.000
I guess we'll see.

27:14.500 --> 27:16.330
What's this?

27:16.330 --> 27:19.710
The precedent that's gonna save
our clients from bankruptcy.

27:19.710 --> 27:23.250
In 1993, a class action
was filed against Trim-Me.

27:23.250 --> 27:24.880
Like all diet pills,
the Trim-Me recipe

27:24.880 --> 27:26.790
is nearly identical
to Gut Suckers' --

27:26.790 --> 27:29.290
caffeine mixed in with
some other inert fillers.

27:29.290 --> 27:31.290
The judge ruled
Trim-Me had to offer

27:31.290 --> 27:34.250
a 50% refund
to every customer.

27:34.250 --> 27:36.500
In exchange,
the company would be protected

27:36.500 --> 27:39.670
from all claims
of damages.

27:39.670 --> 27:43.710
So, I suggest we offer the judge
the Trim-Me precedent.

27:43.710 --> 27:46.040
That way,
instead of paying $100 million

27:46.040 --> 27:48.380
in potential damages,
Gut Suckers pays out

27:48.380 --> 27:51.670
what we've estimated to be
only $5 million.

27:51.670 --> 27:53.620
This is
a rare occurrence,

27:53.620 --> 27:55.710
but I'm actually impressed,
Ms. Castillo.

27:55.710 --> 27:57.330
Good work.

27:57.330 --> 27:59.380
To be honest, I couldn't
have done it without Michaela,

27:59.380 --> 28:01.120
so she deserves
some of your love, too.

28:04.080 --> 28:05.710
I'll make sure
to give you both credit

28:05.710 --> 28:07.080
when I talk
to Mr. Crawford.

28:11.210 --> 28:13.290
Maybe you're the one
who wants to get in her pants.

28:13.290 --> 28:15.670
I would never
steal her away from you.

28:15.670 --> 28:17.040
You killed it.

28:17.040 --> 28:18.580
Thanks.

28:18.580 --> 28:19.880
We'll have to toast you
at the bachelor party.

28:19.880 --> 28:20.880
I didn't invite you.

28:20.880 --> 28:22.580
I know.

28:22.580 --> 28:23.830
Asher did.

28:23.830 --> 28:25.830
I'll see you both there.

28:25.830 --> 28:27.620
How is he
friends with Asher?

28:29.540 --> 28:31.790
No idea.
[ Sighs ]

28:31.790 --> 28:33.790
Under the principle
of stare decisis,

28:33.790 --> 28:36.250
the court must follow
the Trim-Me precedent,

28:36.250 --> 28:38.040
so I just need your approval
to go to the client,

28:38.040 --> 28:39.750
advise them to settle.

28:39.750 --> 28:41.080
If they say yes,

28:41.080 --> 28:43.170
Gut Suckers will be paying
more in our legal fees

28:43.170 --> 28:44.710
than they will
to the customers.

28:46.710 --> 28:49.170
This is the part
where you say, "Great job."

28:50.170 --> 28:51.830
What's going on?

28:51.830 --> 28:53.620
Did Keating accept
the Governor's offer?

28:58.500 --> 28:59.830
She told you about that?

28:59.830 --> 29:01.790
I know everything
that happens in this building.

29:01.790 --> 29:03.580
I also know
what she wants --

29:03.580 --> 29:05.750
it's what we all want --

29:05.750 --> 29:07.540
to be wanted.

29:07.540 --> 29:09.540
'Cause we can't afford
to lose her right now,

29:09.540 --> 29:11.670
especially when I'm out whoring
myself for diet-pill money.

29:13.080 --> 29:15.250
So beg her to stay --

29:15.250 --> 29:17.580
even if that means getting down
on your hands and knees,

29:17.580 --> 29:19.880
'cause that woman's not
gonna stand for anything less.

29:19.880 --> 29:22.080
And honestly,

29:22.080 --> 29:23.670
I kind of love her
for that.

29:23.670 --> 29:26.670
♪♪

29:26.670 --> 29:28.540
Miller: So, I made some calls
about your dad.

29:28.540 --> 29:31.040
The mental-health facility
waiting list is a beast.

29:31.040 --> 29:32.420
That's why I came to you.

29:32.420 --> 29:34.790
Except when you're
the D.A. of Philadelphia

29:34.790 --> 29:36.290
asking for a favor.

29:36.290 --> 29:37.920
They're gonna
transfer your dad

29:37.920 --> 29:40.170
to Wilson Park Hospital
tonight.

29:40.170 --> 29:41.120
It's one of the best
in the state.

29:41.120 --> 29:42.460
He'll be in good hands.

29:44.120 --> 29:45.040
Thanks.

29:46.830 --> 29:48.120
Go tell the old man.

29:50.460 --> 29:52.880
How's Bonnie doing?

29:52.880 --> 29:55.750
It's just a bad flu,

29:55.750 --> 29:56.920
but she'll be
okay soon.

29:58.420 --> 29:59.500
Good.

29:59.500 --> 30:02.540
♪♪

30:02.540 --> 30:05.540
Julie: And all I've done
is try to protect her,

30:05.540 --> 30:07.210
but the only way
I can tell her that

30:07.210 --> 30:10.080
is to risk losing her forever,

30:10.080 --> 30:14.120
'cause if she knew the truth,
it would kill her.

30:16.380 --> 30:18.540
I went through
her record again,

30:18.540 --> 30:19.920
found this.

30:19.920 --> 30:22.620
Julie was arrested
for trespassing in some house

30:22.620 --> 30:26.250
a year after she took the baby
from the hospital.

30:26.250 --> 30:27.790
Same family
lives there --

30:27.790 --> 30:30.580
with a kid the same age
yours would be.

30:32.120 --> 30:33.210
His name's Jake.

30:38.290 --> 30:41.290
Your dad must've
sold the baby to them.

30:41.290 --> 30:44.670
Julie knew,
couldn't help herself, so...

30:44.670 --> 30:46.620
she went to check on him,
and they called the cops.

30:49.170 --> 30:50.580
She knows
who your son is, Bon.

30:50.580 --> 30:52.330
[ Papers rustle ]

30:52.330 --> 30:53.920
She's always known.

30:53.920 --> 31:00.960
♪♪

31:05.290 --> 31:06.380
Joanna:
There you are.

31:07.580 --> 31:09.120
Sorry about this.

31:09.120 --> 31:10.250
We wouldn't have let them
plan the party

31:10.250 --> 31:11.710
if we knew
you were coming --
Sit.

31:26.710 --> 31:28.670
You made this?

31:28.670 --> 31:30.210
Oliver did.

31:30.210 --> 31:31.790
When he was 10.

31:34.000 --> 31:37.540
He was always trying to marry
his Power Rangers.

31:37.540 --> 31:39.290
The other boys
didn't get it.

31:39.290 --> 31:40.330
I didn't get it.

31:42.500 --> 31:46.080
So, when he came out to me
all those years later,

31:46.080 --> 31:48.920
my first thought
was this book,

31:48.920 --> 31:51.000
how he would never get
the wedding he wanted.

31:53.460 --> 31:55.540
I know how much
you mean to my son.

31:57.380 --> 32:01.040
And I can only assume
he means just as much to you.

32:02.500 --> 32:03.960
He does.

32:03.960 --> 32:06.790
He's been through so much,
you know that.

32:09.040 --> 32:11.670
He deserves this.

32:11.670 --> 32:13.120
And so do you.

32:14.880 --> 32:17.210
And I won't be upset

32:17.210 --> 32:19.790
if the ceremony
happens to be in a church.

32:19.790 --> 32:25.880
♪♪

32:25.880 --> 32:27.120
[ Knock on door ]

32:28.620 --> 32:30.420
I still haven't
made my decision.

32:30.420 --> 32:32.120
[ Door closes ]
So hear me out.

32:33.670 --> 32:36.080
I know you think
the only reason I got angry

32:36.080 --> 32:39.210
was because you leaving
would screw me with the board.

32:39.210 --> 32:40.670
That's not
why I got upset.

32:42.170 --> 32:44.330
I admire what you're doing,
Annalise.

32:44.330 --> 32:47.330
That's why I fought the board
to fund your clinic.

32:47.330 --> 32:49.080
And why I looked into
Birkhead's proposal

32:49.080 --> 32:51.210
to see if it was a sham,
which it is.

32:51.210 --> 32:54.210
She's considering
pardoning Nate Senior.

32:54.210 --> 32:55.670
You can't trust her.

32:55.670 --> 32:56.880
But I can trust you?

32:56.880 --> 33:00.080
I can see
why you wouldn't.

33:00.080 --> 33:01.790
I haven't really
been open with you.

33:01.790 --> 33:03.290
I didn't ask you to be.

33:03.290 --> 33:04.420
You shouldn't
have to worry about

33:04.420 --> 33:07.080
who you're working for,
though.

33:07.080 --> 33:12.290
My misconduct wasn't
some gross thing in a copy room.

33:12.290 --> 33:15.040
It was me falling in love
with a client.

33:15.040 --> 33:16.540
I thought
she loved me, too,

33:16.540 --> 33:18.250
but the fact
that it's now labeled

33:18.250 --> 33:21.460
in some H.R. file
as "misconduct"...

33:21.460 --> 33:23.000
Let's just say
that was the firm's way

33:23.000 --> 33:24.580
of protecting themselves.

33:26.290 --> 33:27.830
I'm not a bad guy.

33:27.830 --> 33:29.210
I never said you were.

33:29.210 --> 33:31.500
Then stay.

33:31.500 --> 33:33.830
Please.

33:33.830 --> 33:37.040
Use me to help you
fight this fight.

33:37.040 --> 33:39.170
I promise I will have your back
at every turn.

33:41.290 --> 33:44.460
'Cause I am
more than willing to destroy

33:44.460 --> 33:46.420
whoever gets in your way.

33:46.420 --> 33:51.500
♪♪

33:51.500 --> 33:56.880
♪♪

33:56.880 --> 34:00.210
I cleared my schedule as soon
as I heard you were coming.

34:00.210 --> 34:01.790
I'm turning down
the job.

34:01.790 --> 34:03.080
Why?

34:03.080 --> 34:04.880
Well, I just
don't buy it --

34:04.880 --> 34:06.120
the sudden
change of heart,

34:06.120 --> 34:08.210
the caring about people
who can't vote for you.

34:09.460 --> 34:10.750
You're wrong about me.

34:10.750 --> 34:12.960
I doubt that.

34:12.960 --> 34:15.620
I'm not your enemy,
even though it might be

34:15.620 --> 34:17.920
a hell of a lot easier
for you to see me that way

34:17.920 --> 34:20.250
rather than the person
that I truly am --

34:20.250 --> 34:23.170
an ally
reaching across the aisle

34:23.170 --> 34:25.670
to make
real, positive change

34:25.670 --> 34:27.920
because that is what this world
needs right now.

34:27.920 --> 34:29.540
No.

34:29.540 --> 34:31.710
What the world needs is someone
with no political motives

34:31.710 --> 34:33.250
fighting for
the people in this state

34:33.250 --> 34:34.460
who are
wrongly imprisoned.

34:35.620 --> 34:36.960
That's me.

34:40.790 --> 34:42.960
So, you don't want
to hear about the pardon?

34:45.000 --> 34:48.080
The Board agreed
to free Nathaniel Lahey.

34:48.080 --> 34:50.210
You just need
to accept the job.

34:50.210 --> 34:53.080
♪♪

34:56.620 --> 34:59.420
[ Train whistle blows
in distance ]

35:02.830 --> 35:05.330
All these years, and he was
20 minutes from our house.

35:07.420 --> 35:10.500
Just be honest with me.

35:10.500 --> 35:14.170
Please, just tell me
the truth for once.

35:16.830 --> 35:20.460
Dad was gonna keep him.

35:20.460 --> 35:21.880
At home, with us.

35:23.880 --> 35:29.210
So, on our way back
from the hospital...

35:29.210 --> 35:31.380
we stopped at a light,
and...

35:34.040 --> 35:36.170
...I jumped out of the car
and started running.

35:38.830 --> 35:42.120
I didn't stop
'til I reached that house.

35:42.120 --> 35:45.920
♪♪

35:45.920 --> 35:47.620
And there were woods.

35:47.620 --> 35:51.880
♪♪

35:51.880 --> 35:54.420
And I promised you
I'd protect him.

35:54.420 --> 35:57.960
♪♪

35:57.960 --> 35:59.710
So that's what I did.

35:59.710 --> 36:03.710
♪♪

36:03.710 --> 36:05.620
I buried him.

36:05.620 --> 36:12.540
♪♪

36:16.670 --> 36:19.250
All: 8, 9, 10!

36:19.250 --> 36:20.920
All right,
go, Pam Sandwich!

36:20.920 --> 36:23.120
Trust the gay force!
-Whoo!

36:23.120 --> 36:25.120
-You got this, Pam!
-Whoo-hoo-hoo!

36:25.120 --> 36:26.250
Put those lips
right on his stuff!

36:26.250 --> 36:27.710
[ Indistinct shouting ]

36:27.710 --> 36:30.330
[ Cheers ]

36:30.330 --> 36:31.880
All right, Joanna,
it's your turn.

36:31.880 --> 36:34.580
[ Cheers, laughter ]

36:34.580 --> 36:36.580
-All right!
-Yeah!

36:36.580 --> 36:38.790
Woman: Whoo-hoo!

36:38.790 --> 36:41.290
Hey, Dad. It's me.

36:41.290 --> 36:43.580
If you get a chance,
could you give me a call back?

36:43.580 --> 36:45.330
I wanted to talk
about the wedding.

36:45.330 --> 36:51.380
♪♪

36:51.380 --> 36:53.330
[ Cup clatters ]
Where's li'l man?

36:53.330 --> 36:56.790
Oh, asleep, but I should
go check on him.

36:56.790 --> 36:57.830
I don't like you
that way.

36:57.830 --> 36:59.080
What?

36:59.080 --> 37:00.790
It's why you've been
avoiding me, right?

37:00.790 --> 37:02.710
Relax.
You're not my type.

37:02.710 --> 37:04.580
Plus, I'd never hit on you
knowing it hasn't been that long

37:04.580 --> 37:05.960
since what happened
to Wes.

37:07.330 --> 37:08.830
You know about Wes?

37:08.830 --> 37:10.540
The whole school knows.

37:10.540 --> 37:11.710
But you asked me

37:11.710 --> 37:14.500
if Christopher's dad
was still in the picture.

37:14.500 --> 37:16.000
I only did that
so you didn't think

37:16.000 --> 37:17.460
I was
some creepy stalker.

37:17.460 --> 37:19.620
Well,
now I do think that.

37:19.620 --> 37:20.790
[ Chuckles ]

37:20.790 --> 37:22.710
I'm not.

37:22.710 --> 37:25.670
I'm just sorry about everything
you've gone through.

37:25.670 --> 37:27.380
Asher: [ Amplified ]
Attention, party-goers!

37:27.380 --> 37:28.790
Please make your way
into the living room

37:28.790 --> 37:30.830
for a very important
"safety demonstration"

37:30.830 --> 37:33.210
from Firefighter Freddy.

37:33.210 --> 37:36.250
-Whoo!
-Oww, oww, oww, oww!

37:36.250 --> 37:39.620
-[ Chanting ] Party, party!
-[ Laughs ]

37:39.620 --> 37:41.790
Don't talk to me
anymore.

37:41.790 --> 37:43.210
♪ I never had to doubt ♪

37:43.210 --> 37:45.170
♪ That if you do everything
you said you'd... ♪

37:46.750 --> 37:48.830
You got bumped --

37:48.830 --> 37:51.330
top of the waitlist.
[ Buzzing, door opens ]

37:51.330 --> 37:53.250
They're gonna transfer you
to the new place tonight.

37:53.250 --> 37:54.960
[ Door closes ]
How did you do that?

37:54.960 --> 37:56.170
Pig privileges.

37:56.170 --> 37:57.460
[ Chuckles ]

37:57.460 --> 37:59.250
Here's the address
for your letter.

38:01.620 --> 38:03.790
Reinhoff's got a brother
down in Georgia.

38:03.790 --> 38:04.710
Name's Eugene.

38:06.210 --> 38:07.920
I know
you don't approve...

38:11.330 --> 38:14.750
...but writing this letter

38:14.750 --> 38:16.920
will be the sanest thing
I've done in years.

38:18.710 --> 38:19.920
All right.

38:20.880 --> 38:22.670
Thank you.

38:22.670 --> 38:27.710
Senior: "Dear Eugene,
my name is Nathaniel Lahey,

38:27.710 --> 38:29.460
and I'm the man responsible

38:29.460 --> 38:31.580
for the death
of your brother, Gerald."

38:31.580 --> 38:33.750
[ 2WEI's "Pushin' On" plays ]

38:33.750 --> 38:35.920
"Here I finally am,

38:35.920 --> 38:39.210
writing the apology I should've
a long time ago."

38:40.290 --> 38:44.290
I had every intention
of turning her down.

38:44.290 --> 38:46.750
But then I couldn't.

38:46.750 --> 38:48.330
Not when I could
free the man

38:48.330 --> 38:50.580
whose case
gave me back my career.

38:50.580 --> 38:54.960
♪♪

38:54.960 --> 38:56.830
This job has the power

38:56.830 --> 39:00.460
to help me
do something right and good.

39:00.460 --> 39:03.120
It's bigger than you, me,
this firm.

39:03.120 --> 39:06.830
♪♪

39:06.830 --> 39:08.620
[ Exhales deeply ]

39:08.620 --> 39:11.170
♪♪

39:11.170 --> 39:12.670
So that's
what I'm choosing.

39:12.670 --> 39:22.330
♪♪

39:22.330 --> 39:24.170
I have Ms. Keating
in my office.

39:24.170 --> 39:25.670
Please relieve her
of her badge

39:25.670 --> 39:28.120
and escort her
directly out of the building.

39:28.120 --> 39:30.330
She no longer works here.

39:30.330 --> 39:32.790
♪ I'll be ♪

39:32.790 --> 39:34.500
♪ I'll be pushin' on ♪

39:34.500 --> 39:35.710
♪ Oh ♪

39:35.710 --> 39:38.670
♪ I'll be pushin' on ♪

39:38.670 --> 39:43.170
"I spent the last 30 years
in a cell

39:43.170 --> 39:46.380
thinking I was in pain.

39:46.380 --> 39:49.540
But you've been
in the real pain."

39:49.540 --> 39:51.120
♪♪

39:51.120 --> 39:54.500
"The kind
that never goes away."

39:54.500 --> 39:59.040
♪♪

39:59.040 --> 40:01.290
Who you calling?

40:01.290 --> 40:02.830
Hi, I'd like to report

40:02.830 --> 40:06.290
an unregistered,
unlocked firearm

40:06.290 --> 40:08.080
in a home
where a child lives.

40:08.080 --> 40:09.460
♪♪

40:09.460 --> 40:11.330
[ Cellphone beeps ]

40:11.330 --> 40:14.120
[ Cellphone clatters ]

40:14.120 --> 40:16.580
You'd hate yourself
tomorrow.

40:16.580 --> 40:19.500
"You lost your brother
before his time,

40:19.500 --> 40:22.540
and it was at my hand.

40:22.540 --> 40:28.000
There's no words
to make up for that sin.

40:28.000 --> 40:31.880
I was sure I'd spend
the rest of my days

40:31.880 --> 40:34.120
paying for what I did."

40:35.380 --> 40:39.040
"But then my son
came back to me,

40:39.040 --> 40:40.710
helped me get a second chance."

40:40.710 --> 40:41.750
What's wrong now?

40:41.750 --> 40:43.790
Your dad's
gonna be a free man.

40:43.790 --> 40:45.330
You mean the transfer?

40:45.330 --> 40:48.040
I mean he's gonna be pardoned
by the Governor.

40:49.750 --> 40:51.460
The paperwork
clears in a week,

40:51.460 --> 40:54.960
just enough time to make space
for your new roommate.

40:54.960 --> 40:57.750
"My son chose to love me

40:57.750 --> 41:00.670
in spite of all
the bad things I've done."

41:00.670 --> 41:04.460
♪♪

41:04.460 --> 41:08.000
"I wish I could trade places
with your brother..."

41:08.000 --> 41:09.670
It's time
for your transfer, Lahey.

41:09.670 --> 41:10.790
Van's here.

41:10.790 --> 41:13.540
[ Keys clanging ]

41:13.540 --> 41:15.670
"...give him
the second chance I got."

41:15.670 --> 41:17.670
♪♪

41:17.670 --> 41:19.080
Man: Mr. Lahey?

41:19.080 --> 41:20.580
Yeah, I'm waiting
to talk to my pops.

41:20.580 --> 41:22.040
He there?

41:22.040 --> 41:24.080
Hold a moment.

41:24.080 --> 41:26.880
Senior: "I promise to spend
the rest of my life

41:26.880 --> 41:31.040
carrying the weight of
all the pain I've caused you."

41:31.040 --> 41:32.880
♪ Take ♪

41:32.880 --> 41:34.790
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

41:34.790 --> 41:37.750
Woman: Mr. Lahey, I-I'm afraid
there's been an incident.

41:37.750 --> 41:39.670
What does that mean?
Incident?

41:39.670 --> 41:42.380
♪ Take ♪

41:42.380 --> 41:45.210
Senior:
"Let it go now, sir.

41:46.830 --> 41:49.790
All that pain.

41:49.790 --> 41:53.920
All that grief.

41:53.920 --> 41:55.000
I've got it from here."

41:55.000 --> 41:57.710
♪ I'll be pushin' on, oh ♪

41:57.710 --> 41:59.750
"'Cause that's the least
that I owe you."

41:59.750 --> 42:01.920
♪ I'll be pushin' on, oh ♪

42:01.920 --> 42:03.170
"Sincerely..."

42:03.170 --> 42:06.080
♪♪

42:06.080 --> 42:08.040
"...Nathaniel Lahey Senior."

42:08.040 --> 42:10.670
[ Police radio chatter ]

42:33.000 --> 42:39.580
♪♪

42:39.580 --> 42:46.500
♪♪

42:46.500 --> 42:52.500
♪♪
